.TH "t3_cim_ctl_blk_read" 9 "t3_cim_ctl_blk_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_cim_ctl_blk_read \- read a block from CIM control region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t3_cim_ctl_blk_read
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "unsigned int addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int n "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *valp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "addr" 12
the start address within the CIM control region
.IP "n" 12
number of words to read
.IP "valp" 12
where to store the result

Reads a block of 4-byte words from the CIM control region.
